{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 12 Channel Trimmer\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Individual trimming controls for 12 channels. Useful for (automated) gain control in a parent channel.\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 MSConvert\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Convert a stereo signal either from Mid-Side to AB-format or vice versa. Attenuation of the signal is equally distributed (-3dB) over both conversions, i.e. {\f1 sig->MSConvert->MSConvert == sig} for unity gain values.\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Phase Invert\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 inverts the phase of the second (right) channel.\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Rotate\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Simple utility to alter a stereo signals spatiality. Can be used for rotating an ambisonic B-format sound field around an axis. This effect does an equal power rotation so it also works well on stereo sounds. Inspired by the SuperCollider UGen "Rotate2".\par}
}

